# Age recipients for the commands/.secrets/*.json.age vault files.
#
# Each line is an SSH *public* key that should be able to decrypt the
# vault. Safe to commit — public keys are public by definition.
#
# To add a new machine / identity:
#   1. Append its ssh-rsa or ssh-ed25519 public key below (one per line).
#   2. Re-encrypt every vault file with the new recipient list:
#        age -R commands/.secrets/recipients.txt \
#            -o commands/.secrets/<name>.json.age \
#            commands/.secrets/<name>.json
#   3. Commit the updated ciphertext.
#
# To remove a machine / revoke access:
#   1. Delete that line.
#   2. Re-encrypt every vault file.
#   3. Commit — the old ciphertext is still decryptable by the revoked
#      key, so also **rotate every credential** in the affected vault
#      files on the target services.
#
# You can fetch your GitHub-registered public keys with:
#   curl https://github.com/<username>.keys

